Do you like KLAR that much?

542
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:47,480
Yes.

543
00:34:47,489 --> 00:34:48,489
Why?

544
00:34:48,860 --> 00:34:52,290
I don't know.
I just love being a KLAR marketer.

545
00:34:52,699 --> 00:34:56,580
I love being able to say KLAR is my brand.

546
00:34:57,650 --> 00:35:01,270
I feel especially good

547
00:35:01,270 --> 00:35:02,910
when I see someone using our product.

548
00:35:04,910 --> 00:35:07,180
My first product is lipstick.

549
00:35:07,180 --> 00:35:09,900
I was on a bus

550
00:35:09,940 --> 00:35:12,460
and saw someone taking it out of her bag.

551
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:16,880
I wanted to ask her how she likes it,

552
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:20,550
and tell her that
I'm the one who developed it.

553
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:23,500
It was so hard trying to stay still.

554
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:26,640
Really?

555
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:27,640
Yes.

556
00:35:43,160 --> 00:35:44,000
What?

557
00:35:45,740 --> 00:35:48,040
What?

558
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:50,360
What's with you?

559
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:57,250
Screw this wretched world.

560
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:02,460
Wretched?

561
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:05,260
The world is beautiful. Right?

562
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:10,860
(I'd like to apologize for
my recent post.)

563
00:36:10,860 --> 00:36:14,590
(The KLAR product review was misinformed.)

564
00:36:14,590 --> 00:36:18,760
(I wanted to make it more interesting,)

565
00:36:18,770 --> 00:36:23,790
(and so I exaggerated
some things in my video.)

566
00:36:23,790 --> 00:36:28,570
(I'd like to apologize to all my viewers.)

567
00:36:28,570 --> 00:36:29,690
Okay.

568
00:36:30,850 --> 00:36:34,380
With this apology, things will smooth out.

569
00:36:34,380 --> 00:36:36,400
The return requests died down too.

570
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:37,900
Did you ask the PR team
to release an article?

571
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:40,910
Yes, they'll print that
we won't press charges.

572
00:36:43,350 --> 00:36:47,060
I heard you two worked hard on this.

573
00:36:47,090 --> 00:36:48,460
Well done.

574
00:36:49,150 --> 00:36:50,310
Thank you.

575
00:36:51,040 --> 00:36:53,320
Let's have an office dinner soon.

576
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:54,630
Sounds great.

577
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:56,850
You're dismissed.

578
00:36:56,850 --> 00:36:58,060
Okay.

579
00:36:58,060 --> 00:36:59,330
Thank you.

580
00:37:00,020 --> 00:37:03,100
Give me a moment, ABM Yoon Song-ah.

581
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:12,420
Did you hear from Jae-shin by any chance?

582
00:37:13,120 --> 00:37:16,380
I don't think he'll be contacting me.

583
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:20,150
If he does, could you let me know?

584
00:37:20,480 --> 00:37:22,780
I won't take it the wrong way.

585
00:37:23,630 --> 00:37:24,770
Okay, sir.

586
00:37:26,490 --> 00:37:28,360
Now onto another topic.

587
00:37:30,450 --> 00:37:32,650
Did you receive a job offer recently?

588
00:37:34,940 --> 00:37:38,160
Things might be uncomfortable right now,

589
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:40,400
but I hope you're not going to leave us.

590
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:44,930
You're very much needed at our company.

591
00:37:47,570 --> 00:37:48,720
Thank you.

592
00:37:51,110 --> 00:37:53,430
You need to eat.

593
00:37:53,430 --> 00:37:55,380
It's been days.

594
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:57,890
I don't feel like eating. Go away.

595
00:37:57,890 --> 00:38:00,690
Your brother told me to make sure you eat.

596
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:03,970
Just a little bit.

597
00:38:08,180 --> 00:38:12,220
I'll leave this here then.

598
00:38:12,220 --> 00:38:14,340
Please eat some.

599
00:38:26,060 --> 00:38:26,940
Did you find him?

600
00:38:26,960 --> 00:38:28,930
(His phone has been turned off,)

601
00:38:28,930 --> 00:38:31,560
(and he's not using his credit card.)

602
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:33,750
(It's not easy to track him.)

603
00:38:33,750 --> 00:38:36,620
If it were easy,
I wouldn't have hired you.

604
00:38:37,770 --> 00:38:41,910
I'll pay you more. Just find him!

605
00:38:45,750 --> 00:38:48,180
That's it for the weekly meeting.

606
00:38:48,780 --> 00:38:49,780
Right,

607
00:38:50,220 --> 00:38:54,250
we're getting an intern today.

608
00:38:54,850 --> 00:38:56,300
Already?

609
00:38:56,300 --> 00:38:57,550
I know, right.

610
00:38:57,550 --> 00:39:00,710
Wasn't it yesterday Hyun-seung joined us?

611
00:39:00,710 --> 00:39:04,070
You were so fresh-faced back then.

612
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:07,340
It's only a year,
but I can hardly recognize you already.

613
00:39:11,830 --> 00:39:14,590
Should I break down in tears
right about now?

614
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:15,740
I was joking.

615
00:39:15,750 --> 00:39:19,730
Don't cry.

616
00:39:25,630 --> 00:39:27,070
Right, sir.

617
00:39:27,070 --> 00:39:28,280
I was wondering.

618
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:30,410
The intern's desk.

619
00:39:31,770 --> 00:39:33,330
Where should we put it?

620
00:39:33,330 --> 00:39:35,050
It's best if it's next to you.

621
00:39:35,050 --> 00:39:36,160
But this is the only empty desk we have.

622
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:37,080
Set it up here.

623
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:38,190
Yes, sir.

624
00:39:42,770 --> 00:39:43,600
You want some help?

625
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,210
It's okay. I can do it by myself.

626
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:54,880
Can I have a moment, everyone?

627
00:39:55,340 --> 00:39:57,570
This is Ko Myung-jin.

628
00:39:57,590 --> 00:39:59,080
He'll be our intern for a month.

629
00:39:59,810 --> 00:40:01,370
Hello, I'm Ko Myung-jin.

630
00:40:01,370 --> 00:40:02,690
It's nice to meet you.

631
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:08,740
You can greet him later.

632
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:10,560
Your desk is here.

633
00:40:10,560 --> 00:40:15,450
You'll learn the basics
from ABM Chae Hyun-seung.

634
00:40:15,450 --> 00:40:16,350
Yes, sir.

635
00:40:16,350 --> 00:40:17,390
It's nice to meet you.

636
00:40:17,390 --> 00:40:18,600
Nice to meet you too.

637
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:19,410
Yes.

638
00:40:21,050 --> 00:40:22,160
Myung-jin.

639
00:40:22,630 --> 00:40:23,770
You can sit.

640
00:40:23,910 --> 00:40:24,800
Yes, sir.

641
00:40:31,050 --> 00:40:33,640
Did you learn how to access the internet?

642
00:40:33,670 --> 00:40:34,690
I can show you.

643
00:40:34,710 --> 00:40:36,760
It's okay. I'll figure it out.

644
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:38,870
If you need anything, let me know.

645
00:40:38,870 --> 00:40:41,410
I'll explain our brand
in the meeting room later.

646
00:40:41,420 --> 00:40:42,540
Okay.

647
00:40:45,930 --> 00:40:48,680
I think that covers the brand description.

648
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:51,370
Now about the job assignments
within the team.

649
00:40:51,380 --> 00:40:55,020
There are basic skincare and call sales.

650
00:40:55,020 --> 00:40:57,660
We have color makeup
and department store sales too.

651
00:40:57,800 --> 00:41:00,640
At the same time, we manage PR,

652
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:03,670
inventory management
and visual merchandising.

653
00:41:07,300 --> 00:41:08,950
To put it plainly,

654
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:11,990
our task is to manage all the processes

655
00:41:11,990 --> 00:41:14,890
from product manufacturing to sales.

656
00:41:14,890 --> 00:41:15,890
I see.

657
00:41:17,590 --> 00:41:21,680
Is there anything else
you'd like to know more about?

658
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,450
Feel free to ask.

659
00:41:23,450 --> 00:41:26,120
I had many questions when I was an intern.

660
00:41:27,020 --> 00:41:28,290
I don't have any though.

661
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:32,120
Okay then.

662
00:41:32,950 --> 00:41:34,440
I think we're done here.

663
00:41:34,470 --> 00:41:35,330
Okay.

664
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:42,630
It's close to lunchtime now.

665
00:41:42,630 --> 00:41:44,900
Do you want to join us for lunch?

666
00:41:44,930 --> 00:41:46,250
How about the cafeteria?

667
00:41:46,250 --> 00:41:47,420
I'll eat by myself.

668
00:41:47,430 --> 00:41:48,500
I can do that, right?

669
00:41:49,270 --> 00:41:51,600
Sure, if that's what you want.

670
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:52,910
Thank you.

671
00:41:52,940 --> 00:41:53,820
Okay.

672
00:41:59,270 --> 00:42:00,480
Oh, my god.

673
00:42:00,820 --> 00:42:02,290
You've been turned down?

674
00:42:03,790 --> 00:42:06,710
This is our colleague,
ABM Chae Hyun-seung.

675
00:42:06,710 --> 00:42:07,560
Our interns.

676
00:42:07,560 --> 00:42:08,870
Hello.

677
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:10,500
Hello.

678
00:42:10,500 --> 00:42:12,180
Looking sharp, right?

679
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:14,570
Let's go. I'll save you from eating alone.

680
00:42:14,570 --> 00:42:15,790
Let's go.

681
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:20,880
We're meeting the sales team today.

682
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:24,720
They asked for our input
about their sales promotion.

683
00:42:25,060 --> 00:42:28,020
Marketing usually gives them policies,

684
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:29,750
but sometimes they do their own thing.

685
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:30,790
I see.

686
00:42:33,870 --> 00:42:35,520
Sir.

687
00:42:35,710 --> 00:42:36,470
Yes?

688
00:42:36,470 --> 00:42:37,940
I'll be honest with you.

689
00:42:37,940 --> 00:42:40,350
I'll soon be joining another company.

690
00:42:40,350 --> 00:42:42,300
This is just for the experience.

691
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:44,580
So you don't need to train me.

692
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:50,890
I know.

693
00:42:51,580 --> 00:42:53,280
(Our team's intern said)

694
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:55,960
your intern is going to another company.

695
00:42:55,960 --> 00:42:56,790
Really?

696
00:42:56,810 --> 00:43:00,200
Yes. So don't waste your time on him.

697
00:43:04,390 --> 00:43:08,990
I'm still going to
do my best to train you.

698
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:11,630
That won't make me stay here.

699
00:43:13,300 --> 00:43:16,210
That's not what I'm trying to achieve.

700
00:43:16,890 --> 00:43:19,480
But I learned this from my trainer.

701
00:43:19,860 --> 00:43:24,120
A brand marketer must think that
he is the brand.

702
00:43:24,870 --> 00:43:28,330
When you hear KLAR's name in the future,

703
00:43:28,650 --> 00:43:30,900
I'm sure I will cross your mind.

704
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:34,230
I don't want to be remembered

705
00:43:34,230 --> 00:43:36,960
as an insincere and irresponsible person.

706
00:43:44,730 --> 00:43:45,770
Let's get on.

707
00:43:50,530 --> 00:43:51,430
Ahem.

708
00:44:12,310 --> 00:44:15,960
(Chef Ryu isn't seeing anyone, right?)

709
00:44:16,290 --> 00:44:19,910
No. But I don't think he'd be interested.

710
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:21,320
Marriage isn't his thing.

711
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:23,500
It'd be nice. But…

712
00:44:23,790 --> 00:44:27,030
You can't always get what you want.

713
00:44:27,030 --> 00:44:29,290
What were you two like in college?

714
00:44:30,480 --> 00:44:32,020
I liked him.

715
00:44:40,290 --> 00:44:41,280
Honey.

716
00:44:44,330 --> 00:44:47,030
Are you happy when you are with me?

717
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:50,190
I'm suddenly curious.

718
00:44:50,620 --> 00:44:53,380
I'm happy, are you?

719
00:44:59,250 --> 00:45:00,480
I'm grateful.

720
00:45:02,410 --> 00:45:04,500
Thank you for being my wife.

721
00:45:34,260 --> 00:45:37,150
Do you have something
to say to Hyun-seung?

722
00:45:37,150 --> 00:45:38,540
Gosh.

723
00:45:39,380 --> 00:45:41,540
It's about the brand description.

724
00:45:41,540 --> 00:45:43,690
Can I get the original file?

725
00:45:46,480 --> 00:45:48,290
Okay. Sure.

726
00:45:48,290 --> 00:45:49,890
Thank you.

727
00:45:49,890 --> 00:45:50,920
Also,

728
00:45:51,180 --> 00:45:53,350
can you buy me lunch tomorrow?

729
00:45:53,950 --> 00:45:55,310
At the cafeteria.

730
00:45:56,430 --> 00:45:57,460
Okay.

731
00:45:58,270 --> 00:45:59,340
Sure.

732
00:45:59,340 --> 00:46:00,410
Let's have lunch together tomorrow.

733
00:46:00,410 --> 00:46:02,910
Thank you, Senior Chae!

734
00:46:16,310 --> 00:46:17,440
Bye!

735
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:18,380
Take that home.

736
00:46:18,380 --> 00:46:19,420
Bye!

737
00:46:19,570 --> 00:46:22,270
Bye.

738
00:46:28,530 --> 00:46:29,880
Mommy!

739
00:46:30,650 --> 00:46:31,850
Ha-eun!

740
00:46:31,850 --> 00:46:34,500
Oh? Uncle!

741
00:46:41,080 --> 00:46:42,230
Where's Mommy?

742
00:46:42,230 --> 00:46:46,520
Something came up,
so she asked me to get you.

743
00:46:46,860 --> 00:46:48,080
Is she on a date with Daddy again?

744
00:46:48,080 --> 00:46:50,540
Maybe. What will you do then?

745
00:46:50,540 --> 00:46:53,010
You want to go on a date with me?

746
00:46:53,010 --> 00:46:56,400
Let's go on a date.

747
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:57,610
-Let's do that.
-Sounds good.

748
00:46:57,610 --> 00:46:59,810
Awesome.

749
00:47:03,870 --> 00:47:06,170
How did you grow so tall?

750
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:06,810
Excuse me?

751
00:47:06,810 --> 00:47:08,640
I'm going to grow as tall as you.

752
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:12,200
Ha-eun said she'll marry me
if I become as tall as you.

753
00:47:15,690 --> 00:47:17,170
One moment, please.

754
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:24,440
Marry him?

755
00:47:25,550 --> 00:47:27,350
I was feeling generous.

756
00:47:33,420 --> 00:47:34,430
Just like that?

757
00:47:42,610 --> 00:47:43,930
Why are we standing here?

758
00:47:46,190 --> 00:47:47,470
Just one moment.

759
00:47:57,170 --> 00:47:58,320
Senior Yoon!

760
00:48:04,810 --> 00:48:06,150
Hello, Ha-eun!

761
00:48:07,840 --> 00:48:09,900
Meet my girlfriend.

762
00:48:11,920 --> 00:48:13,810
You finally did it!

763
00:48:16,540 --> 00:48:18,560
Now you know I'm good.

764
00:48:20,210 --> 00:48:21,770
I found it!

765
00:48:22,870 --> 00:48:24,160
You found it!

766
00:48:25,050 --> 00:48:26,320
Should we get the bigger one?

767
00:48:26,320 --> 00:48:29,560
Where are the potatoes? Potatoes.

768
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:30,690
Here they are!

769
00:48:30,690 --> 00:48:32,100
Let's give it to him.

770
00:48:39,730 --> 00:48:41,510
What do you think will be better?

771
00:48:41,510 --> 00:48:43,230
-This one.
-That one?

772
00:48:43,580 --> 00:48:48,120
But that one has a bug in it. A bug!

773
00:48:58,570 --> 00:49:02,710
Which one looks good?

774
00:49:06,710 --> 00:49:08,060
-It's good.
-Is it good?

775
00:49:09,230 --> 00:49:10,380
You're giving me one?

776
00:49:14,150 --> 00:49:15,340
It's very delicious.

777
00:49:16,070 --> 00:49:18,000
Should we ask your uncle to get this?

778
00:49:40,980 --> 00:49:43,920
My uncle buys me many toys.

779
00:49:44,870 --> 00:49:46,200
Really?

780
00:49:47,860 --> 00:49:49,100
Let's dry your hands.

781
00:49:49,940 --> 00:49:52,070
My uncle plays tennis very well.

782
00:49:52,220 --> 00:49:55,270
Oh, I see. That's great.

783
00:49:55,280 --> 00:49:57,360
My uncle listens very well too.

784
00:49:57,360 --> 00:49:59,140
So you did well, Auntie.

785
00:50:01,620 --> 00:50:02,620
Okay.

786
00:50:12,960 --> 00:50:14,220
How is it?

787
00:50:20,350 --> 00:50:22,260
It's so good!

788
00:50:22,260 --> 00:50:24,460
It's delicious. Isn't it, Ha-eun?

789
00:50:24,550 --> 00:50:26,050
I love it.

790
00:50:26,270 --> 00:50:26,990
Is it good?

791
00:50:26,990 --> 00:50:30,700
Eat as much as you want, Ha-eun.

792
00:50:31,820 --> 00:50:33,110
Do you want mussels?

793
00:50:36,260 --> 00:50:37,260
Here.

794
00:50:43,540 --> 00:50:46,180
My hands are tied.

795
00:50:47,710 --> 00:50:48,980
Seriously.

796
00:50:49,330 --> 00:50:50,320
Here.

797
00:50:50,930 --> 00:50:51,930
Thank you.

798
00:50:54,680 --> 00:50:55,930
It's so delicious.

799
00:50:55,930 --> 00:50:57,220
I can sell this.

800
00:51:01,130 --> 00:51:04,200
Who is prettier? Auntie Song-ah or me?

801
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:06,230
You're asking me?

802
00:51:11,380 --> 00:51:14,400
Of course you're prettier, Ha-eun!

803
00:51:16,910 --> 00:51:19,590
You should've said
your girlfriend is prettier.

804
00:51:22,170 --> 00:51:23,640
I'm sorry, Auntie.

805
00:51:23,650 --> 00:51:25,800
My uncle still has a long way to go.

806
00:51:35,850 --> 00:51:37,270
This is my girlfriend.

807
00:51:42,960 --> 00:51:44,880
It's very nice to meet you.

808
00:51:44,880 --> 00:51:48,270
Now I see why Hyun-seung looked all happy.

809
00:51:49,990 --> 00:51:51,210
Open the door for me.

810
00:51:51,210 --> 00:51:51,960
Okay.

811
00:51:54,650 --> 00:51:55,650
Be careful.

812
00:52:03,710 --> 00:52:04,950
Her backpack.

813
00:52:04,950 --> 00:52:06,130
Thank you.

814
00:52:14,380 --> 00:52:16,940
Let's grab dinner
when both of you are free.

815
00:52:16,940 --> 00:52:18,690
It'll be my treat.

816
00:52:19,330 --> 00:52:21,070
That sounds great.

817
00:52:21,830 --> 00:52:24,230
Why is Ha-eun sleeping at your place?

818
00:52:24,230 --> 00:52:27,120
Yeon-seung went to
a funeral with Wu-hyun.

819
00:52:27,120 --> 00:52:28,000
They are out of town.

820
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:31,230
Drive safely.

821
00:52:32,420 --> 00:52:33,630
See you another time.

822
00:52:33,630 --> 00:52:35,680
Sure. Drive safely.

823
00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:37,640
Bye.

824
00:52:49,290 --> 00:52:54,580
She said you buy her toys,
play tennis well

825
00:52:54,870 --> 00:52:56,470
and listen to her well.

826
00:52:56,480 --> 00:53:00,440
Then, she complimented me on my choice.

827
00:53:00,840 --> 00:53:03,560
Ha-eun is very wise for her age.

828
00:53:03,850 --> 00:53:06,390
I'm worried if I set
her standards too high.

829
00:53:07,990 --> 00:53:11,630
But she left out the most important thing.

830
00:53:12,960 --> 00:53:15,420
What I do best is loving Yoon Song-ah.

831
00:53:17,450 --> 00:53:19,330
More like you say
corny things really well.

832
00:53:19,330 --> 00:53:21,050
Action speaks louder than words.

833
00:53:21,720 --> 00:53:22,900
Want me to show you?

834
00:53:28,650 --> 00:53:31,170
Stop it. You're too much.

835
00:54:23,020 --> 00:54:25,270
I'm sorry to show up like this.

836
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:27,840
I really need to tell you something.

837
00:54:28,220 --> 00:54:30,300
Can we talk?

838
00:54:37,970 --> 00:54:39,440
If you must say something,

839
00:54:40,230 --> 00:54:41,560
just say it here.

840
00:54:47,210 --> 00:54:50,280
It's not something
you have to worry about.

841
00:54:51,770 --> 00:54:52,950
Please.

842
00:55:06,630 --> 00:55:08,050
I'll head home.

843
00:55:08,730 --> 00:55:10,070
Call me afterward.

844
00:55:11,230 --> 00:55:12,050
Okay.

845
00:55:49,250 --> 00:55:52,310
You said you wanted to talk.

846
00:56:01,650 --> 00:56:03,290
I was thinking...

847
00:56:04,820 --> 00:56:08,270
I never properly apologized to you.

848
00:56:10,110 --> 00:56:12,120
This may sound like an excuse,

849
00:56:13,440 --> 00:56:16,280
but I didn't mean to keep lying to you.

850
00:56:17,620 --> 00:56:19,520
I wanted to tell you.

851
00:56:20,020 --> 00:56:21,960
But when I was with you,

852
00:56:22,990 --> 00:56:25,020
I could be myself.

853
00:56:27,170 --> 00:56:30,250
I didn't have to be scared that
you'll see the real me.

854
00:56:32,730 --> 00:56:37,500
I could be myself in front of you.

855
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:43,440
I wanted to hold on to you
just one more day.

856
00:56:45,030 --> 00:56:47,690
I thought maybe you'll be understanding.

857
00:56:49,320 --> 00:56:52,330
I was selfish
and let things unravel like that.

858
00:56:52,340 --> 00:56:54,580
Because I was afraid that you'd leave me.

859
00:56:57,100 --> 00:56:59,570
I'm not asking you to forgive me.

860
00:57:00,340 --> 00:57:01,500
I just...

861
00:57:04,200 --> 00:57:05,720
It was real for me.

862
00:57:08,130 --> 00:57:12,050
I'm sorry that it ended the way it did.

863
00:57:16,190 --> 00:57:18,940
I just wanted to tell you this in person.

864
00:57:30,910 --> 00:57:33,020
I heard you resigned.

865
00:57:34,850 --> 00:57:37,040
What will you do from now on?

866
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,620
I haven't thought that far ahead.

867
00:57:39,740 --> 00:57:42,760
I'm going to start over
with what I truly have.

868
00:57:43,440 --> 00:57:45,440
If I've fallen to the bottom,

869
00:57:46,760 --> 00:57:48,430
then that's where I'll start.

870
00:57:51,660 --> 00:57:52,780
By the way,

871
00:57:54,030 --> 00:57:56,630
Jae-woon might find out about our past.

872
00:57:57,650 --> 00:57:59,570
I'll make sure you
won't be treated unfairly.

873
00:57:59,570 --> 00:58:01,980
He already knows.

874
00:58:04,550 --> 00:58:06,090
I hope that didn't cause you trouble.

875
00:58:06,090 --> 00:58:07,440
It didn't.

876
00:58:10,870 --> 00:58:11,970
And also,

877
00:58:13,780 --> 00:58:15,490
don't worry about me.

878
00:58:16,730 --> 00:58:18,550
Not anymore.

879
00:58:21,410 --> 00:58:22,410
Okay.

880
00:58:25,110 --> 00:58:26,360
I understand.

881
00:59:09,320 --> 00:59:10,710
Can I come in?

882
00:59:14,690 --> 00:59:15,670
Come in.

883
00:59:25,900 --> 00:59:27,960
Is everything okay?

884
00:59:28,930 --> 00:59:30,530
Why are you here?

885
00:59:35,240 --> 00:59:37,400
I wanted to see you.

886
00:59:38,270 --> 00:59:39,920
You should've called me.

887
00:59:42,300 --> 00:59:44,310
I didn't want to waste time.

888
00:59:54,170 --> 00:59:57,710
Why are you still unchanged?

889
01:00:00,980 --> 01:00:03,320
Were you staring at
your phone all this time?

890
01:00:03,610 --> 01:00:06,350
I was just doing this and that.

891
01:00:10,820 --> 01:00:12,860
He came to apologize.

892
01:00:15,890 --> 01:00:17,260
Said he was sorry.

893
01:00:24,670 --> 01:00:26,350
I thought this wouldn't bother you.

894
01:00:26,830 --> 01:00:28,900
I never said it doesn't bother me.

895
01:00:29,470 --> 01:00:31,770
How can it not bother me?

896
01:00:31,770 --> 01:00:33,410
You're my girlfriend.

897
01:00:33,410 --> 01:00:37,080
I think about you all the time.
It's crazy.

898
01:00:40,950 --> 01:00:42,220
I'll leave now.

899
01:00:42,400 --> 01:00:43,410
Get some rest.

900
01:00:43,410 --> 01:00:44,690
Already?

901
01:00:44,690 --> 01:00:48,020
I saw the face I wanted to see.
I should go.

902
01:00:48,540 --> 01:00:49,630
Night.

903
01:00:56,930 --> 01:00:59,910
That wasn't enough for me.
Stay for a while.

904
01:01:06,030 --> 01:01:10,090
It's late. How long is a while?

905
01:01:18,780 --> 01:01:19,950
I don't know.
